1
00:00:28,328 --> 00:00:29,488
What is the status?

2
00:00:29,729 --> 00:00:31,297
The area has been expanding at
a constant rate

3
00:00:31,297 --> 00:00:32,457
since we first started monitoring it.

4
00:00:33,099 --> 00:00:35,499
The Stealth Force is already
on its way to investigate.

5
00:00:36,436 --> 00:00:37,903
They should be entering
the area shortly.

6
00:00:39,138 --> 00:00:40,127
I've just established contact.

7
00:00:40,707 --> 00:00:43,109
They'll be passing by the Dangai
Precipice World in ten seconds.

8
00:00:43,109 --> 00:00:45,009
They're about to enter
the dimensional area.

9
00:00:46,179 --> 00:00:47,373
Opening communication lines.

10
00:00:50,883 --> 00:00:53,078
Hey! What--?! The exit!

11
00:00:55,254 --> 00:00:56,380
We have an emergency!

12
00:00:56,956 --> 00:00:58,981
We've failed to infiltrate the area!

13
00:00:59,292 --> 00:01:01,627
Requesting immediate back-up!
I repeat!

14
00:01:01,627 --> 00:01:02,855
We have an emergency!

15
00:01:02,895 --> 00:01:04,764
- The infiltration has failed!
- Research T echnology Com mcenter here.

16
00:01:04,764 --> 00:01:06,165
We copy your back-up request.

17
00:01:06,165 --> 00:01:07,325
This is Research
Technology Commcenter..

18
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:09,096
Requesting emergency opening
of Senkaimon.

19
00:01:09,469 --> 00:01:12,238
Members of the Stealth Force
have failed to infiltrate the area!

20
00:01:12,238 --> 00:01:14,536
- Notify Central 46 immediately!
- They have been left behind...

21
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,700
- Move!
- in the Dangai Precipice World.

22
00:01:15,775 --> 00:01:17,868
We'll be swallowed up by
the Restrictive Current!

23
00:01:17,977 --> 00:01:19,412
Hey! Can you hear me?

24
00:01:19,412 --> 00:01:22,745
Why can't you infiltrate the area?
Tell us!

25
00:02:27,413 --> 00:02:28,903
- Get ready!
- Right!

26
00:02:31,918 --> 00:02:32,816
Hey!

27
00:02:48,801 --> 00:02:49,699
You're not getting away!

28
00:03:25,938 --> 00:03:26,836
Not so easy!

29
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,082
Ichigo!

30
00:03:45,691 --> 00:03:48,785
It seems that Hollow
was after this child.

31
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:57,928
It's all right. He only looks scary.

32
00:03:58,037 --> 00:03:59,061
Shut up!

33
00:04:01,407 --> 00:04:02,635
All right then, let's go.

34
00:04:03,442 --> 00:04:04,744
Don't worry.

35
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:07,645
Soul Society is not a scary place.

36
00:04:08,548 --> 00:04:10,140
It's where all the souls
come from.

37
00:04:12,184 --> 00:04:12,946
But...

38
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:16,122
If you stay here...

39
00:04:16,122 --> 00:04:18,590
another monster like that
will come after you.

40
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:11,069
Is it over already?

41
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:12,040
Yes.

42
00:05:12,578 --> 00:05:13,476
Thanks.

43
00:05:15,781 --> 00:05:16,770
Ichigo!

44
00:05:16,849 --> 00:05:17,816
Huh?

45
00:05:18,618 --> 00:05:20,779
Don't use your Combat Pass
so freely.

46
00:05:21,087 --> 00:05:22,611
Huh? Why?

47
00:05:24,323 --> 00:05:25,620
Oww!

48
00:05:26,225 --> 00:05:27,249
What's the big idea?!

49
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:33,528
You have him.

50
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,869
You keep leaving your body
here and there,

51
00:05:36,869 --> 00:05:39,429
and thanks to that, I'm the one who has
to deal with the messy aftermath.

52
00:05:39,572 --> 00:05:40,539
Why's that?

53
00:05:40,606 --> 00:05:41,834
For example...

54
00:05:42,141 --> 00:05:43,904
A passerby approaches.

55
00:05:44,043 --> 00:05:49,071
"Excuse me, is something wrong?
Oh no, this man isn't breathing!"

56
00:05:49,482 --> 00:05:53,441
"Ambulance. No, if he's dead,
I must get a hearse!"

57
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,178
Get the idea?

58
00:05:55,287 --> 00:05:57,414
Like they'd call a hearse!

59
00:05:57,657 --> 00:05:58,791
That's not the point!

60
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:02,488
In any case, it's a big hassle
if there's a commotion.

61
00:06:02,561 --> 00:06:03,323
Huh?

62
00:06:04,063 --> 00:06:06,258
Hurry! He's in cardiac arrest!

63
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:08,825
Too late...

64
00:06:09,001 --> 00:06:10,730
M-My body!

65
00:06:12,338 --> 00:06:13,862
Oh, look!

66
00:06:13,939 --> 00:06:15,907
What's going on?!

67
00:06:16,008 --> 00:06:17,270
He's alive!

68
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,238
You..!

69
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,901
Uh, hi.

70
00:06:20,246 --> 00:06:21,178
Are you all right?

71
00:06:23,115 --> 00:06:24,605
You still need to lie down!

72
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:25,945
I'm telling you, I'm fine!

73
00:06:26,085 --> 00:06:28,417
- Hey, hold him down! He's delirious!
- Stop it!

74
00:06:28,454 --> 00:06:29,443
Really...

75
00:06:39,131 --> 00:06:40,689
Man, that was bad.

76
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,427
That's my line!

77
00:06:43,135 --> 00:06:45,037
You're lucky I had
my Memory Replacement

78
00:06:45,037 --> 00:06:46,698
to switch everyone's memory.

79
00:06:46,972 --> 00:06:47,495
Kon!

80
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:48,968
Yes, yes!

81
00:06:49,508 --> 00:06:50,133
Hey...

82
00:06:50,876 --> 00:06:51,577
What's with you?!

83
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:54,341
- Why, Sis?!
- There's no point unless you hold him!

84
00:06:54,814 --> 00:06:56,215
- No, no way!
- Why do I wanna...!

85
00:06:56,215 --> 00:06:57,807
Sis, I absolutely...!

86
00:06:58,584 --> 00:06:59,414
Shut up!

87
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:02,046
What?

88
00:07:02,154 --> 00:07:04,557
- S-Stop! I'll get dirty!
- Shut up!

89
00:07:04,557 --> 00:07:06,320
There's dog poop over there!

90
00:07:06,358 --> 00:07:07,450
Hope it sticks to you!

91
00:07:07,593 --> 00:07:09,458
What's the meaning of this?

92
00:07:09,962 --> 00:07:11,827
What? Another Hollow?

93
00:07:12,331 --> 00:07:13,025
Take this!

94
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,792
It got in my mouth!

95
00:07:16,068 --> 00:07:16,898
Ichigo...

96
00:07:17,703 --> 00:07:19,364
Serves you right!

97
00:07:19,472 --> 00:07:21,702
Why you--!
You've done it this time!

98
00:07:21,807 --> 00:07:23,798
- S-Stop! My stuffing's gonna fall out!
- Hey!

99
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:25,470
Wait! I'm dealing with him...

100
00:07:25,711 --> 00:07:26,609
Huh?

101
00:07:28,147 --> 00:07:29,079
The train station!

102
00:07:29,381 --> 00:07:30,143
Hey!

103
00:07:33,152 --> 00:07:34,517
What's with this Spiritual Pressure?

104
00:07:34,854 --> 00:07:35,752
I don't know.

105
00:07:36,188 --> 00:07:38,349
I've never experienced this kind
of Spiritual Pressure before.

106
00:08:20,065 --> 00:08:21,794
What the hell are they?

107
00:08:22,101 --> 00:08:24,001
White ghosts?!

108
00:08:26,238 --> 00:08:28,229
No one else can see them.

109
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:30,569
They must be spirit beings.

110
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:33,704
But they don't have chains
on their chests.

111
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,278
What's...

112
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:36,640
We have no choice.

113
00:08:37,349 --> 00:08:39,044
What? Again?

114
00:08:40,486 --> 00:08:41,646
Use him!

115
00:08:43,956 --> 00:08:45,924
Huh?! Hey, what--?!

116
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:48,952
Disgusting...

117
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:55,464
Kon! Go hide somewhere!

118
00:08:56,402 --> 00:08:57,426
Hey!

119
00:08:57,536 --> 00:08:59,163
Hey, don't leave me...!

120
00:09:00,639 --> 00:09:02,869
Hey, what are you doing?!

121
00:09:03,576 --> 00:09:05,678
This is Rukia Kuchiki of Squad 1 3,

122
00:09:05,678 --> 00:09:08,010
in World of the Living area 3888!

123
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,910
Rukia!

124
00:09:08,948 --> 00:09:11,075
Ichigo, try performing a Konso!

125
00:09:11,183 --> 00:09:12,548
What?! A Konso?!

126
00:09:12,618 --> 00:09:13,744
Reporting on the situation!

127
00:09:14,286 --> 00:09:16,755
- Unidentified spirit beings...
- What the hell... It's worth a try.

128
00:09:16,755 --> 00:09:18,416
possessing spiritual power
have appeared in large numbers.

129
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:25,187
No good Rukia!
It's not working on these guys...

130
00:09:25,431 --> 00:09:28,958
Wait! My connection with Soul Society...

131
00:09:36,775 --> 00:09:38,936
What's going on?! Huh?

132
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:42,079
Huh?! Stop!

133
00:09:42,147 --> 00:09:43,045
Rukia!

134
00:09:44,516 --> 00:09:48,145
What's this all of a sudden?!
Stop! Stop!

135
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:50,379
What's the deal with you guys?!
Move it!

136
00:09:53,893 --> 00:09:54,882
What'll we do?

137
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:56,293
Well...

138
00:10:03,869 --> 00:10:04,699
What the--?!

139
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:16,103
A Soul Reaper?!

140
00:10:16,615 --> 00:10:18,173
What are you doing?!

141
00:10:18,918 --> 00:10:19,850
Hey!

142
00:10:27,226 --> 00:10:30,457
Oww! Oww!
Hey, don't step on me!

143
00:10:33,832 --> 00:10:34,764
Huh?!

144
00:10:36,402 --> 00:10:37,801
What's that?

145
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:49,771
She's going to release her zanpaku-to!

146
00:10:49,882 --> 00:10:50,780
What?!

147
00:10:51,383 --> 00:10:52,941
Bring them to the twilight...

148
00:10:56,689 --> 00:10:57,519
Ichigo!

149
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:00,819
Stop! What the hell are you doing?!

150
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:03,128
Those things aren't Hollows!

151
00:11:03,696 --> 00:11:05,129
Shut your mouth, stupid!

152
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:05,960
Stu...?!

153
00:11:10,803 --> 00:11:13,169
Hey! You stepped on my face...

154
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,000
Bring them to the twilight!

155
00:11:16,308 --> 00:11:17,434
Mirokumaru!

156
00:11:24,450 --> 00:11:25,382
What?!

157
00:11:25,818 --> 00:11:28,082
Now what?

158
00:11:29,521 --> 00:11:31,785
Huh? What happened to
that other guy?

159
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:56,870
Sorry to keep you waiting!
Wasn't that wind so strong?

160
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:05,690
What's going on?

161
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:06,525
They vanished.

162
00:12:06,525 --> 00:12:08,254
Yes! That was awesome!

163
00:12:09,028 --> 00:12:12,794
Yes, yes, yes! That felt so good!

164
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:16,231
Oh, it's you.

165
00:12:18,103 --> 00:12:19,070
YOU!

166
00:12:19,338 --> 00:12:22,068
H-How'd you change into
your gigai so quickly?

167
00:12:22,374 --> 00:12:23,342
I dunno.

168
00:12:23,342 --> 00:12:24,934
Just who are you?

169
00:12:25,344 --> 00:12:26,402
I'm a Soul Reaper.

170
00:12:26,845 --> 00:12:28,506
I know that!

171
00:12:28,881 --> 00:12:32,078
If you want to know someone's name,
shouldn't you introduce yourself first?

172
00:12:34,053 --> 00:12:35,418
I'm lchigo Kurosaki.

173
00:12:36,188 --> 00:12:37,780
Oh, you're pretty obedient.

174
00:12:38,157 --> 00:12:40,426
My name is Senna. Later!

175
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:41,688
Don't "Later" me!

176
00:12:42,094 --> 00:12:43,561
Why'd you do such a thing?

177
00:12:43,962 --> 00:12:45,486
Why not?

178
00:12:45,998 --> 00:12:48,660
Do you know something
about those things?

179
00:12:50,502 --> 00:12:51,703
Hey! What's the matter?

180
00:12:51,703 --> 00:12:53,500
This is bad! I knew it!

181
00:12:53,806 --> 00:12:54,670
What is it?!

182
00:12:55,674 --> 00:12:59,474
Hmm... Yellow just isn't my color.

183
00:13:00,045 --> 00:13:02,445
Never mind that. Come!

184
00:13:03,482 --> 00:13:04,642
Ichigo, right?

185
00:13:04,817 --> 00:13:05,579
Yeah.

186
00:13:06,685 --> 00:13:07,947
- Over there!
- Huh?

187
00:13:08,387 --> 00:13:09,788
There's an unconscious man...

188
00:13:09,788 --> 00:13:11,990
in front of the train station.
Requesting an ambulance immediately!

189
00:13:11,990 --> 00:13:13,981
Kon! Not again!

190
00:13:14,193 --> 00:13:16,058
See, you better hurry!

191
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:18,760
Not so fast! Come with me!

192
00:13:19,198 --> 00:13:20,222
Hey!

193
00:13:20,432 --> 00:13:21,865
I just want to ask you some questions!

194
00:13:23,335 --> 00:13:24,495
The fool...

195
00:13:46,592 --> 00:13:47,957
Give up already?

196
00:13:49,094 --> 00:13:50,425
You gotta be kidding!

197
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:53,699
I don't know...

198
00:13:53,699 --> 00:13:55,400
You really think it's okay
for a lieutenant

199
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,628
to be drinking in
the middle of the day?

200
00:13:57,436 --> 00:14:00,928
What're you saying?
This is like drinking water.

201
00:14:01,373 --> 00:14:03,342
Hey! It's emptied out already.

202
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,310
What?! Not again!

203
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:08,105
You drink too much,
you shaded geezer!

204
00:14:08,647 --> 00:14:10,274
Shut up, baldie!

205
00:14:10,415 --> 00:14:11,905
What?!

206
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:13,352
Wanna go another round?!

207
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:17,220
Fine! Whoever loses gets the sake.
Got it?!

208
00:14:19,625 --> 00:14:21,149
Taking the high ground again?

209
00:14:22,427 --> 00:14:23,894
The quicker one gets it!

210
00:14:25,063 --> 00:14:27,395
Whatever. Here l...

211
00:14:27,799 --> 00:14:28,527
Huh?

212
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,430
What's the matter?!

213
00:14:33,438 --> 00:14:34,735
What is that thing?

214
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:51,881
A Ferris wheel! Look!

215
00:14:54,026 --> 00:14:55,891
I didn't know they had
one of these here.

216
00:14:58,564 --> 00:14:59,792
Wow...

217
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:03,902
Anyway, what were you saying?

218
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:05,369
What squad do you belong to?!

219
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:08,039
I don't remember such things.

220
00:15:08,740 --> 00:15:11,174
Hmm... What squad did I belong to?

221
00:15:11,677 --> 00:15:12,811
Listen here.

222
00:15:12,811 --> 00:15:15,914
You wield a zanpaku-to
and know how to release it.

223
00:15:15,914 --> 00:15:18,314
There is no question that
you are a Soul Reaper.

224
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:21,947
And if you are a Soul Reaper,
you must belong to a squad!

225
00:15:22,321 --> 00:15:23,948
How can you not remember that?

226
00:15:24,189 --> 00:15:25,554
Question, please!

227
00:15:25,991 --> 00:15:28,186
Why are you here?

228
00:15:29,194 --> 00:15:30,092
Well, that's...

229
00:15:31,496 --> 00:15:32,485
Hey!

230
00:15:32,631 --> 00:15:34,622
I said I forgot!

231
00:15:36,201 --> 00:15:37,498
What does it matter, anyway?

232
00:15:38,103 --> 00:15:40,571
Then do you know what
those guys were back there?

233
00:15:41,039 --> 00:15:42,472
Don't know that either.

234
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:45,344
Oh, he's so cute! Can I pet him?

235
00:15:45,344 --> 00:15:46,106
Sure.

236
00:15:47,512 --> 00:15:50,174
But I thought I should
take care of them that way.

237
00:15:51,516 --> 00:15:52,574
Instinct.

238
00:15:53,952 --> 00:15:55,510
You know what I mean?

239
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:58,654
What's with her?!

240
00:15:58,890 --> 00:16:01,984
Ichigo, I'm going to Soul Society.

241
00:16:02,194 --> 00:16:03,024
Huh?

242
00:16:03,295 --> 00:16:04,853
I'm having trouble contacting them.

243
00:16:06,231 --> 00:16:08,665
And I'm concerned about
the phenomenon earlier, too.

244
00:16:09,201 --> 00:16:11,863
Do not let that girl out of your sight!

245
00:16:12,504 --> 00:16:15,107
Hey you! Trying to dump it on me...!

246
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:16,335
Sis... Not again...

247
00:16:17,676 --> 00:16:18,777
I'm counting on you.

248
00:16:18,777 --> 00:16:21,439
Boy, what's she so uptight about?

249
00:16:22,714 --> 00:16:24,181
Hey lchigo!

250
00:16:24,316 --> 00:16:26,341
Stupid, don't shout like that here!

251
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:27,317
She's gone!

252
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:29,283
What?! Dammit!

253
00:16:32,024 --> 00:16:32,922
Hey!

254
00:16:33,258 --> 00:16:34,748
Jeez, you're so persistent!

255
00:16:37,362 --> 00:16:39,023
Hey, wait!

256
00:16:46,305 --> 00:16:47,329
Hey!

257
00:16:52,110 --> 00:16:53,077
Oh?

258
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:58,250
Remember when you told me
that if I answered your questions,

259
00:16:58,250 --> 00:16:59,740
you'd do anything I asked you to?

260
00:17:00,585 --> 00:17:01,847
I never said anything like that!

261
00:17:03,255 --> 00:17:04,654
Let's play tag!

262
00:17:06,258 --> 00:17:07,748
Hey! I told you! I never said such thing.

263
00:17:09,695 --> 00:17:10,923
Wait!

264
00:17:16,134 --> 00:17:17,692
Jeez!

265
00:17:19,271 --> 00:17:20,761
Hey, come on out!

266
00:17:21,406 --> 00:17:22,395
Where'd you go?

267
00:17:22,474 --> 00:17:24,408
Hey, what's with all
the fun and games?

268
00:17:24,476 --> 00:17:24,999
Huh?

269
00:17:27,646 --> 00:17:29,341
Rangiku! Toshiro!

270
00:17:29,781 --> 00:17:30,805
It's been a while...

271
00:17:30,949 --> 00:17:33,941
It's not Toshiro.
Address me as Captain Hitsugaya!

272
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,254
What're you two doing here anyway?

273
00:17:37,789 --> 00:17:38,983
Wait up!

274
00:17:39,057 --> 00:17:40,149
We need to talk.

275
00:17:40,625 --> 00:17:42,786
Err, well, now's not...

276
00:17:42,894 --> 00:17:44,156
Just come!

277
00:17:44,496 --> 00:17:45,622
H-Hey!

278
00:17:46,264 --> 00:17:48,255
Hey! Dammit!

279
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,598
I'll come back. You wait!

280
00:17:53,472 --> 00:17:56,134
That man is talking to himself.

281
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:03,482
I see...

282
00:18:03,482 --> 00:18:05,814
Rukia went to Soul Society?

283
00:18:06,651 --> 00:18:08,084
You just missed her then.

284
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:11,882
Well, where shall we start?

285
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:13,992
At 1 2:50 a.m. today,

286
00:18:13,992 --> 00:18:17,655
a town from the World of the Living
suddenly appeared above the Seireitei.

287
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:20,198
At the same time, the Research
Technology Commcenter detected

288
00:18:20,198 --> 00:18:22,367
a trail of spiritual waves flowing
into the World of the Living,

289
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:23,668
and one minute later,

290
00:18:23,668 --> 00:18:25,863
we lost all communication
between the two worlds.

291
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:28,667
What're you talking about?

292
00:18:29,107 --> 00:18:30,165
Don't you even understand this much?

293
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,470
Now now...

294
00:18:31,710 --> 00:18:34,270
I'll explain it to you in a simple manner.

295
00:18:34,746 --> 00:18:36,548
First off, our universe has two worlds,

296
00:18:36,548 --> 00:18:40,211
which are the World of the Living,
where we are, and the Soul Society.

297
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:43,054
Between them is
the Dangai Precipice World,

298
00:18:43,054 --> 00:18:47,150
to keep the two worlds from colliding.

299
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:49,958
You ran through it once.
Remember?

300
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:53,899
However, about three days ago,
a new dimension appeared

301
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:57,469
between the Dangai Precipice World
and the World of the Living.

302
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:58,670
It began to expand rapidly,

303
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:01,298
bridging the gap and adhering
to both worlds.

304
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:05,877
At this point, it appears the area
that attached itself is acting like a lens

305
00:19:05,877 --> 00:19:08,780
and the World of the Living is
being visible from the Soul Society,

306
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,806
which is in a different dimension.

307
00:19:12,517 --> 00:19:15,111
I guess you can say it's like a mirage.

308
00:19:15,353 --> 00:19:18,924
The Stealth Force was sent out to
investigate this newly created dimension,

309
00:19:18,924 --> 00:19:20,391
but they failed.

310
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:22,060
Our only choice now is...

311
00:19:22,060 --> 00:19:25,325
to check out the influx of spiritual waves
into the World of the Living.

312
00:19:25,797 --> 00:19:28,459
It was decided that
I would head up the operation.

313
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:30,665
Why you?

314
00:19:31,703 --> 00:19:33,728
The other captains backed out.

315
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:36,370
Never mind that!

316
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,777
Then it was probably those guys.

317
00:19:40,245 --> 00:19:41,473
You saw something?

318
00:19:41,713 --> 00:19:46,412
Yeah... hoards of 'em,
all white wearing pointy red hats.

319
00:19:47,419 --> 00:19:48,886
Blanks....

320
00:19:49,287 --> 00:19:50,982
As suspected,
the Valley of Screams.

321
00:19:51,356 --> 00:19:52,254
Huh?

322
00:19:53,225 --> 00:19:56,023
All right then.
Explanation Number Two. Ready?

323
00:19:57,429 --> 00:19:59,164
As you already know,
souls migrate between

324
00:19:59,164 --> 00:20:02,065
the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

325
00:20:02,501 --> 00:20:04,436
From time to time however,
some may, for example,

326
00:20:04,436 --> 00:20:06,238
encounter accidents
in the Dangai Precipice World

327
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:09,139
and become detached
from this Cycle of T ransmigration.

328
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:12,911
These souls wander aimlessly
through the Dangai Precipice World

329
00:20:12,911 --> 00:20:15,436
and are slowly drawn together
over a period of time.

330
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:18,679
As the souls come together,
it causes a new dimension.

331
00:20:19,217 --> 00:20:20,912
It is known as the Valley of Screams.

332
00:20:21,853 --> 00:20:23,188
In the Valley of Screams,

333
00:20:23,188 --> 00:20:25,657
the souls separate into
memory and energy

334
00:20:25,657 --> 00:20:28,353
in preparation to return to
the Cycle of T ransmigration.

335
00:20:29,461 --> 00:20:30,928
Are you following me?

336
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:32,087
I'm following!

337
00:20:33,098 --> 00:20:39,367
Kurosaki, the ones you saw were
the souls with no memory, Blanks.

338
00:20:40,138 --> 00:20:42,470
What happens to the memories?

339
00:20:42,607 --> 00:20:44,743
It's said that the memories
merge together into one entity

340
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:47,576
and returns to the World of the Living.

341
00:20:47,712 --> 00:20:49,548
Hence, it is called a Shinenju.

342
00:20:49,548 --> 00:20:52,483
That is the name for
the collective of memories.

343
00:20:52,784 --> 00:20:53,852
In any case,

344
00:20:53,852 --> 00:20:56,154
the appearance of the Valley of Screams
is a natural phenomenon,

345
00:20:56,154 --> 00:20:59,123
and it's existence has been
verified a number of times...

346
00:20:59,558 --> 00:21:01,355
But the problem is...

347
00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:03,795
This time, the Valley of Screams
has connected

348
00:21:03,795 --> 00:21:07,959
the World of the Living
and the Soul Society.

349
00:21:08,466 --> 00:21:10,366
Is it that unnatural?

350
00:21:10,869 --> 00:21:15,033
There's no way a tunnel connecting
two stars can be created naturally!

351
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:16,869
This is the same thing!

352
00:21:17,542 --> 00:21:20,010
There's no doubt that someone
is doing this deliberately.

353
00:21:20,812 --> 00:21:22,746
Hey! Speaking of which...!

354
00:21:24,649 --> 00:21:26,014
Huh? What is it?

355
00:21:26,618 --> 00:21:30,554
There were some guys wearing
strange armor with those white monsters!

356
00:21:30,689 --> 00:21:31,849
I saw it!

357
00:21:32,357 --> 00:21:33,221
Armor?

358
00:21:33,325 --> 00:21:36,089
Do you remember it in more detail?

359
00:21:36,194 --> 00:21:38,321
Of course, I remember!

360
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:41,899
Uhh... now let's see.

361
00:21:43,435 --> 00:21:45,869
I remember... I mean...

362
00:21:48,607 --> 00:21:51,041
Let me analyze this.

363
00:21:51,176 --> 00:21:52,370
Yes, please do.

364
00:21:53,445 --> 00:21:56,615
Anyway, if this is being
done intentionally,

365
00:21:56,615 --> 00:21:58,139
then it is done with a grudge.

366
00:21:58,249 --> 00:21:59,443
What do they want?

367
00:21:59,718 --> 00:22:02,744
Well, I don't know. It's just...

368
00:22:03,288 --> 00:22:05,423
I have this feeling...

369
00:22:05,423 --> 00:22:08,393
that they're looking for
the Shinenju that has returned

370
00:22:08,393 --> 00:22:10,258
to the World of the Living.

371
00:22:11,463 --> 00:22:12,862
That's my hunch.

372
00:22:15,900 --> 00:22:18,664
We'll try to identify the enemy.

373
00:22:19,137 --> 00:22:21,298
Kurosaki, please keep
watch over the town.

374
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,536
They are bound to appear again.

375
00:22:25,443 --> 00:22:27,934
And, if possible...find the Shinenju.

376
00:22:29,414 --> 00:22:30,849
Yeah, but...

377
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,680
I still have to find that girl, too...

378
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:34,215
Oh, sorry!

379
00:22:45,397 --> 00:22:46,989
What should I do?

380
00:22:47,465 --> 00:22:49,558
Wow! You really came back?!

381
00:22:50,368 --> 00:22:51,960
Over here! Over here!

382
00:22:58,943 --> 00:23:02,003
Of course! I still have questions
I wanna ask.

383
00:23:02,147 --> 00:23:04,843
Fine! Let's pick up where we left off!
You're it!

384
00:23:05,817 --> 00:23:07,682
Hey, listen...!

385
00:23:11,156 --> 00:23:12,180
That little...!

386
00:23:21,132 --> 00:23:23,368
All right... here goes with
the legendary performance!

387
00:23:23,368 --> 00:23:25,131
Take a deep breath...!

388
00:23:25,837 --> 00:23:27,964
Ready, and go!

389
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:30,174
Ten, nine, eight, seven, six,
five, four, three, two, one!

390
00:23:30,241 --> 00:23:32,436
- It's all gone!
- Well done!

391
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:33,703
Wasn't that too fast?!

392
00:23:33,845 --> 00:23:35,938
No such thing. It's good!

393
00:23:36,448 --> 00:23:38,473
All...

394
00:23:39,317 --> 00:23:40,215
right!

395
00:23:56,134 --> 00:23:57,465
Over there! Up there!

396
00:23:58,103 --> 00:23:58,899
Senna...!

397
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:00,332
Hey...

398
00:24:00,739 --> 00:24:02,036
- What's that?
- Huh?!

399
00:24:04,776 --> 00:24:06,175
What's she doing?

400
00:24:06,377 --> 00:24:07,605
Is it some kind of act?

401
00:24:27,532 --> 00:24:28,931
This feels so nice.

402
00:24:47,252 --> 00:24:48,412
Where'd she go?

403
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:49,919
She disappeared!

404
00:24:50,188 --> 00:24:51,450
No, in the back!

405
00:24:53,224 --> 00:24:54,782
Yay!

406
00:24:55,627 --> 00:24:56,958
Yay!

407
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:00,154
- How was that, everyone?!
- Uh... hi.

408
00:25:01,866 --> 00:25:03,060
C'mon, join me!

409
00:25:03,101 --> 00:25:04,864
Err... Later.

410
00:25:07,305 --> 00:25:09,865
No fair, they're getting
more attention than us!

411
00:25:12,343 --> 00:25:14,106
Thanks for the meal!

412
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:18,817
You should've just told me.

413
00:25:18,817 --> 00:25:21,547
If you'd said you were treating,
I'd have answered anything!

414
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:25,178
You didn't have any money?

415
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:28,819
So what about it?

416
00:25:28,993 --> 00:25:30,426
What about what?

417
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,356
I just explained it to you.

418
00:25:32,997 --> 00:25:36,933
Is there anything you know about
the Blanks and the Shinenju?

419
00:25:37,202 --> 00:25:38,499
Nope, I don't know anything.

420
00:25:38,570 --> 00:25:39,901
It's the first I've heard of them.

421
00:25:41,072 --> 00:25:44,235
So someone used
those pointy-hat things to...

422
00:25:44,776 --> 00:25:46,767
what was it again?

423
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:48,205
Shinenju.

424
00:25:48,346 --> 00:25:50,371
Look for that thing, right?

425
00:25:50,615 --> 00:25:51,343
Yeah.

426
00:25:51,683 --> 00:25:53,116
So who is this someone?

427
00:25:53,685 --> 00:25:55,277
We're checking into that, too.

428
00:25:55,753 --> 00:25:57,015
For what?

429
00:25:57,655 --> 00:25:58,587
I dunno.

430
00:25:59,390 --> 00:26:01,551
Have you got any idea what
this Shinenju looks like?

431
00:26:02,794 --> 00:26:03,920
Not a clue.

432
00:26:04,662 --> 00:26:06,391
You're no help at all.

433
00:26:06,731 --> 00:26:11,225
You just have to wait until
the pointy-hats appear again, right?

434
00:26:13,605 --> 00:26:15,630
Oh well, I'll help.

435
00:26:15,707 --> 00:26:16,503
Huh?

436
00:26:17,642 --> 00:26:19,473
But in return...

437
00:26:19,544 --> 00:26:20,670
I knew it!

438
00:26:21,112 --> 00:26:21,908
That!

439
00:26:22,046 --> 00:26:23,013
That?

440
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:26,149
Take me for a ride on that and
I'll help you with whatever you want!

441
00:26:27,285 --> 00:26:29,048
I'm not fallin' for that again.

442
00:26:29,721 --> 00:26:30,745
Hey!

443
00:26:31,789 --> 00:26:34,121
You love heights, don't you?

444
00:26:34,459 --> 00:26:37,095
If you look at things from above,

445
00:26:37,095 --> 00:26:41,429
all the things that seem confusing
or messed up... suddenly become clear.

446
00:26:41,966 --> 00:26:43,661
Hey, that ribbon.

447
00:26:43,835 --> 00:26:48,169
Oh, you noticed?
Don't you think red is cuter?

448
00:26:48,306 --> 00:26:50,103
I don't mean that.
How'd you get it?

449
00:26:50,742 --> 00:26:54,542
I saw it in some shop and tried it on...

450
00:26:55,246 --> 00:26:57,448
I was looking at other things,
and forgot about it.

451
00:26:57,448 --> 00:26:58,574
It happens often, doesn't it?

452
00:26:58,683 --> 00:27:00,116
No way! Come with me!

453
00:27:01,019 --> 00:27:02,384
What about the tab here?

454
00:27:09,994 --> 00:27:11,052
I'd like to buy this.

455
00:27:11,963 --> 00:27:13,590
A present for your girlfriend?

456
00:27:14,198 --> 00:27:15,165
No!

457
00:27:15,433 --> 00:27:16,900
I'll gift wrap it for you.

458
00:27:17,502 --> 00:27:18,935
I'll take it as is!

459
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:21,996
- Here.
- Oh...

460
00:27:23,308 --> 00:27:24,639
Thank you!

461
00:27:28,613 --> 00:27:29,477
Here.

462
00:27:29,914 --> 00:27:33,145
You're unexpectedly uptight,
actually going back to pay for it.

463
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:37,017
Shut up! I hate that kind of thing.

464
00:27:37,522 --> 00:27:39,456
Thank you! What about
the Ferris wheel?

465
00:27:39,590 --> 00:27:41,080
Absolutely not.

466
00:27:41,159 --> 00:27:42,057
Meany!

467
00:27:42,226 --> 00:27:44,717
High-schoolers don't have
that much money.

468
00:27:46,798 --> 00:27:47,594
Hey!

469
00:27:47,799 --> 00:27:49,790
Shut up. I'm just going to the restroom!

470
00:28:00,812 --> 00:28:02,074
Okay...

471
00:28:03,915 --> 00:28:05,314
He's quite nice.

472
00:28:06,751 --> 00:28:08,378
There! All right!

473
00:28:20,431 --> 00:28:21,523
That river...

474
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:30,204
Dad!

475
00:28:32,043 --> 00:28:33,271
Welcome home!

476
00:28:44,989 --> 00:28:46,183
Dad...?

477
00:28:49,027 --> 00:28:51,029
You were late tonight, huh?

478
00:28:51,029 --> 00:28:52,397
Mom, I'm hungry!

479
00:28:52,397 --> 00:28:53,989
I know. Take your seat.

480
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:55,729
Okay then, cheers!

481
00:29:07,779 --> 00:29:09,508
What's taking so long?! Huh?

482
00:29:11,716 --> 00:29:12,512
Huh?!

483
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:17,354
This place was
so crowded a minute ago.

484
00:29:57,628 --> 00:30:00,256
This... is my...

485
00:30:04,802 --> 00:30:06,235
This is my funeral?

486
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:10,866
Dad? Mom?

487
00:30:19,217 --> 00:30:20,809
They are from earlier...

488
00:30:23,921 --> 00:30:24,649
What?!

489
00:30:29,293 --> 00:30:30,521
Now what?!

490
00:30:31,662 --> 00:30:34,062
You've got better reflexes
than I expected.

491
00:30:37,268 --> 00:30:38,667
What do you want with me?

492
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:44,798
Come with us.
Our lord, Ganryu, summons you!

493
00:30:45,209 --> 00:30:47,973
Ganryu? Never heard of him.

494
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:53,074
There's no need for you to know him,
since you are the...

495
00:30:53,184 --> 00:30:54,048
Jai!

496
00:30:55,653 --> 00:30:57,917
I told you not to blab.

497
00:30:59,157 --> 00:31:01,148
Jumping out like that...

498
00:31:03,628 --> 00:31:05,528
I'll catch her in an instant.

499
00:31:09,167 --> 00:31:11,362
Oh, that tickles.

500
00:31:19,043 --> 00:31:20,203
Don't crush her.

501
00:31:20,645 --> 00:31:22,613
Hurry it up. Let's go.

502
00:31:30,488 --> 00:31:32,479
Now then, let's go.

503
00:31:33,491 --> 00:31:34,355
Hold it!

504
00:31:35,893 --> 00:31:37,190
Where do you think you're going?

505
00:31:38,963 --> 00:31:40,988
You...Where did you come from?!

506
00:31:45,269 --> 00:31:47,601
My arm... my arm!

507
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:50,635
What's with all the wandering off?

508
00:31:51,042 --> 00:31:52,009
Ichigo...

509
00:31:52,376 --> 00:31:53,570
That's my own business!

510
00:31:54,579 --> 00:31:57,776
No way.
You're gonna keep your promise.

511
00:31:59,350 --> 00:32:01,511
Hey, big guy. Sorry about that.

512
00:32:01,652 --> 00:32:04,177
You won't get away with this!
I won't let you!

513
00:32:04,255 --> 00:32:05,984
Jai! Enough.

514
00:32:07,792 --> 00:32:09,851
It is not yet the time.

515
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:13,727
Time? What're you talking about?

516
00:32:13,898 --> 00:32:14,830
Dammit!

517
00:32:15,700 --> 00:32:16,632
Hey, hold on!

518
00:32:20,204 --> 00:32:21,262
Hey!

519
00:32:21,906 --> 00:32:24,340
You let someone treat you,
then run off?

520
00:32:24,375 --> 00:32:25,603
I didn't run away!

521
00:32:26,277 --> 00:32:27,141
Then what?

522
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:30,908
My family grave is here.

523
00:32:31,182 --> 00:32:32,809
Cut the crap.

524
00:32:33,217 --> 00:32:36,186
It's true. I remember it.

525
00:32:37,488 --> 00:32:40,184
It's hazy,
but I remember when I was alive.

526
00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:42,990
That's why I came here for a look.

527
00:32:44,095 --> 00:32:45,722
My house used to be around here, too.

528
00:32:47,598 --> 00:32:51,193
I'll help you tomorrow for sure.
I'm not lying.

529
00:32:51,802 --> 00:32:52,496
See you!

530
00:32:53,170 --> 00:32:54,330
You idiot.

531
00:32:54,405 --> 00:32:57,033
Like I can abandon someone
who was just attacked.

532
00:33:02,346 --> 00:33:05,474
Bad guys are after her? That's fishy.

533
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:07,785
Well, at any rate,

534
00:33:07,785 --> 00:33:09,946
it's just for one night.

535
00:33:10,888 --> 00:33:11,980
I'm Senna.

536
00:33:12,657 --> 00:33:15,490
I'm Yuzu Kurosaki. Welcome.

537
00:33:15,726 --> 00:33:16,886
Thanks for having me.

538
00:33:17,194 --> 00:33:20,220
Hey Yuzu, let her sleep in your room.

539
00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:21,962
And let her bathe, too.

540
00:33:22,099 --> 00:33:23,259
- Bathe?!
- Okay.

541
00:33:28,572 --> 00:33:29,834
What's the matter, Dad?

542
00:33:30,608 --> 00:33:31,836
Hey! Yuzu, you too?

543
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:36,210
Come in until your bed's ready.

544
00:33:37,615 --> 00:33:40,778
Hmm... Boys' rooms are
always so drab and boring.

545
00:33:40,951 --> 00:33:41,883
Don't start.

546
00:33:44,588 --> 00:33:46,453
It seems like you've got
a nice family though.

547
00:33:46,557 --> 00:33:47,353
You think?

548
00:33:48,292 --> 00:33:49,953
My dad too. He was...

549
00:33:58,903 --> 00:33:59,460
Hey!

550
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:01,868
Huh?

551
00:34:02,206 --> 00:34:03,173
What's the matter?

552
00:34:03,441 --> 00:34:05,909
Oh, nothing.

553
00:34:06,110 --> 00:34:09,238
By the way, why were
those guys after you?

554
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:10,772
Did they say anything?

555
00:34:11,148 --> 00:34:16,279
Hmm.... Something about Gan-whatever
wanted me brought to him.

556
00:34:16,587 --> 00:34:17,246
And?

557
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:21,119
That's all. If you hadn't come by,
I might've learned more.

558
00:34:21,459 --> 00:34:22,483
What?!

559
00:34:22,727 --> 00:34:24,661
Hey, don't sleep in my bed!

560
00:34:24,762 --> 00:34:26,787
- Why? There's nothing wrong with it.
- Of course there is!

561
00:34:27,131 --> 00:34:28,189
Hey, don't lift your legs up!

562
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:29,961
- You're such a bother!
- No, I'm not!

563
00:34:30,034 --> 00:34:31,524
Stop it!

564
00:34:31,635 --> 00:34:34,604
Shh! She says
she's gonna sleep in his bed!

565
00:34:34,638 --> 00:34:36,697
Well, lchigo is a man, after all.

566
00:34:36,774 --> 00:34:37,575
Nooo!

567
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:39,744
Oh, Masaki, it's the day
we've been dreading!

568
00:34:39,744 --> 00:34:41,541
What am I to do?

569
00:34:42,113 --> 00:34:44,513
Hey! What's goin' on out here?

570
00:34:44,682 --> 00:34:46,115
See, he's all mad.

571
00:34:46,183 --> 00:34:48,651
The bath is ready.

572
00:34:49,353 --> 00:34:50,547
Cripes!

573
00:34:52,089 --> 00:34:54,580
Hey Senna, take a bath
and then go to sleep.

574
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:56,590
Hey!

575
00:35:08,139 --> 00:35:10,300
Kurosaki, it's me Urahara.

576
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:14,339
Any leads on the Shinenju?

577
00:35:14,812 --> 00:35:19,647
Nope. But I encountered
the enemy Kon was talking about.

578
00:35:19,984 --> 00:35:20,848
Are you hurt?

579
00:35:21,318 --> 00:35:24,253
I'm fine. They took off right away.

580
00:35:25,156 --> 00:35:25,952
I see.

581
00:35:26,657 --> 00:35:30,354
About that, we were able to turn up
a few things up on our end.

582
00:35:30,728 --> 00:35:31,353
What?

583
00:35:32,062 --> 00:35:35,332
After analyzing the visual images
taken from Kon's memories...

584
00:35:35,332 --> 00:35:39,496
We identified the armor
as belonging to the clan

585
00:35:40,438 --> 00:35:44,308
that was banished long time ago
from the Soul Society

586
00:35:44,308 --> 00:35:46,640
after their take-over attempt failed.

587
00:35:48,012 --> 00:35:51,778
So we know for sure that
they hold a grudge against us.

588
00:35:52,583 --> 00:35:55,518
But we still don't know
what they're after.

589
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:59,153
Urahara, can I ask you one thing?

590
00:35:59,957 --> 00:36:01,015
What is it?

591
00:36:01,792 --> 00:36:06,627
Can a Soul Reaper have memories
of when they were alive?

592
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:10,566
Let's see... I doubt that very much.

593
00:36:11,068 --> 00:36:12,695
Why do you ask?

594
00:36:14,371 --> 00:36:17,397
No reason... Just curious.

595
00:36:26,517 --> 00:36:29,213
Say, do you really think
they'll show up again?

596
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:30,509
I dunno...

597
00:36:30,588 --> 00:36:34,820
But the only lead we have is
that we saw the Blanks here.

598
00:36:35,159 --> 00:36:36,786
Boring.

599
00:36:36,894 --> 00:36:39,362
Man, why so many people?

600
00:36:41,131 --> 00:36:43,998
It's usually less crowded around
this time of hour...

601
00:36:50,474 --> 00:36:53,102
Senna, don't go too far
from my side.

602
00:36:54,411 --> 00:36:55,378
Hey!

603
00:36:59,149 --> 00:37:00,241
Hey Senna!

604
00:37:00,351 --> 00:37:01,318
Over here!

605
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:02,352
Huh?

606
00:37:07,124 --> 00:37:11,390
You were just attacked yesterday!
Don't go wandering off like that!

607
00:37:14,298 --> 00:37:14,992
A soul?

608
00:37:17,434 --> 00:37:18,696
Hey, what's the matter?

609
00:37:21,105 --> 00:37:22,402
You're scaring him.

610
00:37:25,075 --> 00:37:28,135
My name's Senna. What's yours?

611
00:37:28,946 --> 00:37:29,970
Tomoya.

612
00:37:30,281 --> 00:37:31,509
Tomoya, huh?

613
00:37:32,016 --> 00:37:34,484
Will you tell me what's wrong?

614
00:37:34,885 --> 00:37:39,481
Umm... My dad's gone...

615
00:37:40,391 --> 00:37:42,757
You were with your dad?

616
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:47,197
Uh-huh. We were driving to the festival,

617
00:37:47,197 --> 00:37:49,961
but when I looked,
he was gone.

618
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,030
I see...

619
00:37:51,368 --> 00:37:52,392
Well then...

620
00:37:52,903 --> 00:37:56,339
Your dad is probably in heaven and...

621
00:37:56,707 --> 00:37:57,867
That's not true!

622
00:37:58,609 --> 00:38:00,668
Dad is looking for me!

623
00:38:01,211 --> 00:38:02,075
Okay!

624
00:38:02,346 --> 00:38:05,008
Then we'll help you find your dad.

625
00:38:05,215 --> 00:38:05,977
Really?

626
00:38:06,116 --> 00:38:07,515
Of course!

627
00:38:08,085 --> 00:38:10,076
Tomoya, which way
did you come from?

628
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:10,984
Over that way!

629
00:38:11,088 --> 00:38:12,214
Then let's go.

630
00:38:12,289 --> 00:38:13,085
Hey!

631
00:38:13,824 --> 00:38:15,621
Hey! Right now, we have to...

632
00:38:15,693 --> 00:38:17,752
But we have no leads, right?

633
00:38:17,895 --> 00:38:20,329
No sense in hanging around here.
Let's go.

634
00:38:20,364 --> 00:38:21,058
Okay!

635
00:39:21,859 --> 00:39:23,850
Hey, how long're you gonna
keep at it?

636
00:39:25,429 --> 00:39:27,329
There's no festival around here.

637
00:39:29,199 --> 00:39:30,567
Besides...

638
00:39:30,567 --> 00:39:32,967
there's no guarantee that
his father is still on this side.

639
00:39:33,103 --> 00:39:34,070
We'll find him.

640
00:39:34,905 --> 00:39:41,208
That boy has to leave this world soon.
And a long journey awaits him...

641
00:39:42,513 --> 00:39:46,779
It's his last wish.
How sad if it doesn't come true.

642
00:39:47,718 --> 00:39:50,585
I can't bring myself to perform
a Konso like this.

643
00:39:56,527 --> 00:39:57,789
I want to at least give him...

644
00:39:58,662 --> 00:40:01,028
a good last memory.

645
00:40:01,331 --> 00:40:02,764
Sis!

646
00:40:03,267 --> 00:40:04,256
What is it?

647
00:40:06,170 --> 00:40:08,604
Sis! This way! This way!

648
00:40:28,692 --> 00:40:31,388
Sis... My dad...

649
00:40:31,528 --> 00:40:33,860
Don't worry. Let's find him.

650
00:40:33,964 --> 00:40:34,931
Okay.

651
00:40:38,102 --> 00:40:40,195
I'm so glad this place is still here.

652
00:40:41,004 --> 00:40:42,972
I came here a lot as a child.

653
00:40:44,274 --> 00:40:45,104
You...

654
00:40:46,009 --> 00:40:46,873
Tomoya.

655
00:40:48,312 --> 00:40:49,472
Tomoya!

656
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,338
Dad!

657
00:40:54,218 --> 00:40:55,185
Dad...

658
00:40:59,757 --> 00:41:02,317
I'm sorry... I'm so sorry.

659
00:41:06,563 --> 00:41:07,962
I don't believe this...

660
00:41:09,533 --> 00:41:10,761
Thank you so much!

661
00:41:11,034 --> 00:41:12,092
I'm happy for you.

662
00:41:12,269 --> 00:41:13,133
Uh-huh.

663
00:41:15,005 --> 00:41:16,233
It's all thanks to you.

664
00:41:16,807 --> 00:41:19,640
No, I didn't do anything.

665
00:41:21,311 --> 00:41:26,214
I see. Could it be that
you haven't noticed?

666
00:41:26,917 --> 00:41:31,149
All these souls gathered
around you here.

667
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:35,853
I was able to find this place
thanks to them.

668
00:41:37,394 --> 00:41:38,952
These people...?

669
00:41:39,730 --> 00:41:42,995
Uh-huh...all of them here.

670
00:41:43,767 --> 00:41:46,736
How weird. You're the one
who called them here.

671
00:41:47,204 --> 00:41:50,139
Tomoya...
now we can go on our journey.

672
00:41:50,774 --> 00:41:51,900
Bye bye.

673
00:41:54,578 --> 00:41:55,272
Hey!

674
00:42:03,353 --> 00:42:05,218
Hey! Wait a minute.

675
00:42:08,492 --> 00:42:09,322
These guys...?!

676
00:42:14,198 --> 00:42:15,130
Why...

677
00:42:19,770 --> 00:42:22,034
Why do they come around me?

678
00:42:28,312 --> 00:42:32,408
Ichigo... I'm actually...

679
00:42:33,884 --> 00:42:34,782
I'm...

680
00:42:37,888 --> 00:42:38,820
Senna...

681
00:42:51,869 --> 00:42:52,995
Ukitake?

682
00:42:53,804 --> 00:42:54,793
What's wrong?

683
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:58,598
What happened, Rukia?

684
00:42:59,243 --> 00:43:00,107
Well...

685
00:43:01,678 --> 00:43:05,136
This is a Level
One order from Central 46.

686
00:43:05,415 --> 00:43:07,576
Ichigo, hand over that girl!

687
00:43:07,751 --> 00:43:08,479
What?!

688
00:43:09,386 --> 00:43:13,257
Ichigo, I went through every record of
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads,

689
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:17,785
the Stealth Force, the Kido Force,
and the Soul Reaper Academy...

690
00:43:18,195 --> 00:43:19,958
There is no Senna listed anywhere!

691
00:43:21,198 --> 00:43:24,768
And the zanpaku-to
the girl uses, Mirokumaru...

692
00:43:24,768 --> 00:43:27,671
It has been verified that it was
swallowed up by the Restrictive Current

693
00:43:27,671 --> 00:43:30,037
in the Dangai Precipice World
1 00 years ago along with its owner.

694
00:43:31,208 --> 00:43:34,837
In other words,
it cannot possibly exist today.

695
00:43:35,545 --> 00:43:38,446
Wait a minute!
What are you saying?

696
00:43:39,416 --> 00:43:41,145
I'm a Soul Reaper...

697
00:43:41,385 --> 00:43:44,286
Then when did you come to
the World of the Living?

698
00:43:44,955 --> 00:43:49,983
Well... two days ago I woke up
by the banks of that river.

699
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:53,158
But I remember my own name clearly.

700
00:43:53,931 --> 00:43:57,025
And that river...
I've known it since I was a child...

701
00:43:58,068 --> 00:43:59,330
But... why?

702
00:44:00,337 --> 00:44:02,271
I'm supposed to be just me....

703
00:44:02,539 --> 00:44:05,997
See? All kinds of memories are
mixed up in your head, right?

704
00:44:07,044 --> 00:44:08,909
It's hard to believe...

705
00:44:09,479 --> 00:44:13,245
But the collective of memories
you are searching for, the Shinenju,

706
00:44:13,550 --> 00:44:14,448
is you.

707
00:44:17,387 --> 00:44:18,411
I'm...

708
00:44:19,489 --> 00:44:22,151
The Valley of Screams became
visible twenty-four hours ago....

709
00:44:22,826 --> 00:44:25,395
Soul Society has concluded that
the man behind it is Ganryu

710
00:44:25,395 --> 00:44:27,264
and his motive is to destroy the worlds...

711
00:44:27,264 --> 00:44:31,724
and that a crucial element
in his plans is the Shinenju.

712
00:44:33,036 --> 00:44:34,264
The Shinenju Senna!

713
00:44:36,039 --> 00:44:39,531
Soul Society will now take
you into custody!

714
00:44:41,945 --> 00:44:44,937
That's ridiculous?!
What are you saying?

715
00:44:45,816 --> 00:44:46,908
I'm...

716
00:44:47,584 --> 00:44:49,017
Even I'm...!

717
00:44:49,252 --> 00:44:50,014
I...!

718
00:44:50,487 --> 00:44:53,217
Hold it. It just doesn't
sit well with me.

719
00:44:53,657 --> 00:44:55,522
Ichigo, what are you..?!

720
00:44:56,526 --> 00:44:58,595
No matter what this girl is,

721
00:44:58,595 --> 00:45:00,688
it doesn't change the fact that
she exists at this moment.

722
00:45:01,231 --> 00:45:03,734
She gets mad, she gets happy,
she gets hurt...

723
00:45:03,734 --> 00:45:05,258
she has feelings, doesn't she?

724
00:45:06,403 --> 00:45:08,530
But you're gonna ignore that
and take her into custody?!

725
00:45:09,339 --> 00:45:11,807
Then you're no different from them!

726
00:45:13,276 --> 00:45:15,608
I'm not handing Senna over to you.

727
00:45:16,747 --> 00:45:19,944
Sorry, but this is not the time to debate.

728
00:45:20,250 --> 00:45:21,911
Move, lchigo!

729
00:45:23,587 --> 00:45:24,884
Can't do that.

730
00:45:29,593 --> 00:45:30,958
What's that?!

731
00:45:42,506 --> 00:45:43,302
Renji!

732
00:45:44,307 --> 00:45:45,069
Matsumoto!

733
00:45:59,756 --> 00:46:01,747
These guys!

734
00:46:03,026 --> 00:46:03,958
Behind you!

735
00:46:10,567 --> 00:46:14,765
Hey kid... Today, you will turn
the Shinenju over to us.

736
00:46:15,939 --> 00:46:19,067
Hah! You wanna lose
your other arm too?!

737
00:46:19,543 --> 00:46:20,373
Ichigo!

738
00:46:20,577 --> 00:46:22,067
- Kon, take care of her!
- Right!

739
00:46:36,093 --> 00:46:38,493
He has much more power
than yesterday!

740
00:46:44,768 --> 00:46:46,065
Protect the Shinenju!

741
00:46:46,536 --> 00:46:47,127
Yes ma'am!

742
00:46:49,573 --> 00:46:50,972
What are these things?!

743
00:46:52,409 --> 00:46:55,469
Reign over the frosted heavens!
Hyorinmaru!

744
00:47:06,823 --> 00:47:09,257
Roar! Zabimaru!

745
00:47:10,827 --> 00:47:11,816
What?!

746
00:47:16,233 --> 00:47:17,530
Sogyonokotowari!

747
00:47:18,301 --> 00:47:19,859
- Go, Kuchiki!
- Yes, sir!

748
00:47:20,170 --> 00:47:21,762
Get outta the way!

749
00:47:23,306 --> 00:47:24,364
Sis!

750
00:47:24,741 --> 00:47:26,834
Hado 33: Sokatsui!

751
00:47:27,777 --> 00:47:28,675
You're in my way!

752
00:47:29,946 --> 00:47:30,469
Hey!

753
00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:33,509
I am a Soul Reaper!

754
00:47:39,923 --> 00:47:41,447
Bring them to the twilight!

755
00:47:42,325 --> 00:47:43,189
Don't!

756
00:47:43,293 --> 00:47:44,419
Mirokumaru!

757
00:47:54,538 --> 00:47:55,368
Senna!

758
00:47:59,342 --> 00:48:00,741
As I suspected.

759
00:48:01,611 --> 00:48:03,947
That pattern on the armor belongs
to the banished clan...

760
00:48:03,947 --> 00:48:05,676
The once noble House of Ryodoji!

761
00:48:06,650 --> 00:48:07,981
I wouldn't know.

762
00:48:09,352 --> 00:48:12,549
We are from the Clan of Darkness,
the Dark One.

763
00:48:13,957 --> 00:48:15,015
What?!

764
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:16,790
You won't get away!

765
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:32,909
Let's go.

766
00:48:44,254 --> 00:48:45,983
You've got some nerve!

767
00:48:49,125 --> 00:48:50,319
Hey, let go of me!

768
00:48:50,794 --> 00:48:51,590
Senna!

769
00:48:53,263 --> 00:48:54,230
I'm coming for you!

770
00:49:01,238 --> 00:49:03,468
I won't hand Senna over!

771
00:49:09,746 --> 00:49:10,576
You're mine...!

772
00:49:18,722 --> 00:49:21,520
Ichigo? Ichigo!

773
00:49:31,001 --> 00:49:32,195
Ichigo!

774
00:49:34,771 --> 00:49:36,432
Nooo!

775
00:49:42,212 --> 00:49:43,110
Ichigo!

776
00:49:46,016 --> 00:49:46,778
Ichigo!

777
00:50:07,304 --> 00:50:08,271
He's okay now.

778
00:50:09,406 --> 00:50:12,170
Thank you.
I'm glad you all came to help.

779
00:50:12,475 --> 00:50:14,340
Sheesh, he's hopeless.

780
00:50:15,278 --> 00:50:16,677
No such thing.

781
00:50:17,380 --> 00:50:18,748
It was a surprise attack,

782
00:50:18,748 --> 00:50:21,774
but still there were three squad captains
and even they couldn't fend them off.

783
00:50:22,686 --> 00:50:23,618
It couldn't be helped.

784
00:50:23,853 --> 00:50:24,785
Boss...

785
00:50:24,921 --> 00:50:26,013
What about the squad members?

786
00:50:26,489 --> 00:50:29,549
Unfortunately, they lost track
of the enemy.

787
00:50:32,529 --> 00:50:34,394
Have you been able to learn
anything else?

788
00:50:34,497 --> 00:50:37,200
Yes, it seems they plan to use
the power of the Shinenju

789
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:41,471
to pull the World of the Living
and the Soul Society together

790
00:50:41,471 --> 00:50:43,336
to make them collide.

791
00:50:44,641 --> 00:50:45,733
No way...!

792
00:50:46,176 --> 00:50:50,169
It's hard to believe.
But that's the only explanation.

793
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:51,977
What about the Soul Society?

794
00:50:52,415 --> 00:50:56,784
They should be working on
the next plan of action. Just...

795
00:50:57,220 --> 00:50:59,723
It's not possible to access
the Valley of Screams

796
00:50:59,723 --> 00:51:01,156
from the Soul Society.

797
00:51:02,092 --> 00:51:05,289
Without an entryway,
it's impossible to enter another world.

798
00:51:06,429 --> 00:51:07,589
Isn't there any other way?

799
00:51:08,598 --> 00:51:11,534
Well, there should be an entrance
in the World of the Living,

800
00:51:11,534 --> 00:51:15,436
which was created
when the Shinenju appeared.

801
00:51:15,872 --> 00:51:16,566
I see.

802
00:51:17,841 --> 00:51:18,569
Ichigo!

803
00:51:19,809 --> 00:51:22,471
If we find the entrance,
we can go after them.

804
00:51:24,981 --> 00:51:26,642
Right, Urahara?

805
00:51:27,917 --> 00:51:28,849
Yes.

806
00:51:30,053 --> 00:51:30,951
Let's go!

807
00:51:33,356 --> 00:51:34,118
Ichigo!

808
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:39,320
We have no choice.
Let's go and search, too.

809
00:51:39,529 --> 00:51:40,359
- Right!
- Yes!

810
00:51:45,602 --> 00:51:47,036
As for the cause of the explosion,

811
00:51:47,036 --> 00:51:49,596
there are no traces of any gunpowder
or chemical residue.

812
00:51:49,973 --> 00:51:51,907
Hmmm...
What is going on here?!

813
00:52:16,733 --> 00:52:18,667
Ichigo... I...

814
00:52:19,436 --> 00:52:22,428
It's not your fault.

815
00:52:24,541 --> 00:52:27,908
She's self-centered and stubborn
and a little crazy...

816
00:52:30,280 --> 00:52:31,406
But she was trembling.

817
00:52:36,186 --> 00:52:38,788
Deep down, she was frightened...

818
00:52:38,788 --> 00:52:40,517
that she didn't know who
she really was.

819
00:52:43,793 --> 00:52:44,987
And yet...

820
00:52:47,063 --> 00:52:48,530
And yet, I couldn't protect her.

821
00:52:51,201 --> 00:52:55,831
Oh, you noticed?
Don't you think red is cuter?

822
00:52:56,773 --> 00:52:58,842
Remember when you told me that
if I answered your questions,

823
00:52:58,842 --> 00:53:01,208
you'd do anything I asked you to?

824
00:53:01,911 --> 00:53:04,280
If you look at things from above,

825
00:53:04,280 --> 00:53:07,050
all the things that seem confusing
or messed up...

826
00:53:07,050 --> 00:53:08,381
suddenly become clear.

827
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:13,118
Why'd she say that...?

828
00:53:17,727 --> 00:53:19,319
Ichigo, what's wrong?

829
00:53:19,662 --> 00:53:21,357
Rukia, come with me.

830
00:53:21,564 --> 00:53:22,326
O-Okay.

831
00:53:51,561 --> 00:53:55,122
I remember when I was alive.

832
00:53:56,165 --> 00:53:57,689
My house used to be
around here, too.

833
00:53:59,035 --> 00:54:01,265
There... in the river.

834
00:54:15,885 --> 00:54:16,783
What is that?!

835
00:54:21,190 --> 00:54:25,149
This is the same phenomenon
that's visible from the Soul Society!

836
00:54:25,895 --> 00:54:26,793
We can go through it!

837
00:54:27,430 --> 00:54:29,921
Rukia, contact Urahara.

838
00:54:30,233 --> 00:54:32,599
W-Wait, lchigo! You can't go alone...

839
00:54:32,702 --> 00:54:33,566
I'm going!

840
00:54:35,305 --> 00:54:36,897
I'm gonna...

841
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:38,805
save her no matter what!

842
00:54:39,309 --> 00:54:39,968
Ichigo!

843
00:55:37,300 --> 00:55:38,494
What is this place...?

844
00:55:38,901 --> 00:55:41,699
I thought you wanted me to do
something for you!

845
00:55:42,538 --> 00:55:45,274
There's nothing for you to do.
We just need you...

846
00:55:45,274 --> 00:55:48,038
to be the instrument through
which we fulfill our dream.

847
00:55:48,511 --> 00:55:49,842
What are you talking about?!

848
00:55:49,979 --> 00:55:51,571
Lower your voice!

849
00:55:51,948 --> 00:55:56,578
Lord Ganryu is the rightful ruler
of Soul Society!

850
00:55:57,320 --> 00:56:00,756
It's all right. I abandoned
such formalities long ago.

851
00:56:02,325 --> 00:56:05,161
One thousand years have passed
since my grandfather

852
00:56:05,161 --> 00:56:08,221
gave in to the unjust laws
and was banished from Soul Society.

853
00:56:08,631 --> 00:56:12,735
We wandered in exile in
this Dangai Precipice World...

854
00:56:12,735 --> 00:56:15,638
and survived by evading
the Restrictive Current,

855
00:56:15,638 --> 00:56:17,663
which swallows up everything
that touches it.

856
00:56:19,709 --> 00:56:21,277
We learned a way to utilize the souls

857
00:56:21,277 --> 00:56:23,513
who had strayed from
the Cycle of T ransmigration

858
00:56:23,513 --> 00:56:27,617
and turned into wandering ghosts
in the Dangai Precipice World

859
00:56:27,617 --> 00:56:31,383
as a source of power.

860
00:56:35,191 --> 00:56:37,625
The number of souls is
always constant.

861
00:56:40,596 --> 00:56:44,934
Therefore, when these souls,
or "Blanks" who have strayed

862
00:56:44,934 --> 00:56:47,170
from the Cycle of
T ransmigration reach a certain number...

863
00:56:47,170 --> 00:56:50,506
they're naturally drawn together
and generate a dimension

864
00:56:50,506 --> 00:56:52,474
known as the Valley of Screams.

865
00:56:52,775 --> 00:56:57,235
In other words, this space was
created by countless Blanks.

866
00:56:57,780 --> 00:56:59,015
And at the same time,

867
00:56:59,015 --> 00:57:02,652
all the memories of these lost souls
merge into one object

868
00:57:02,652 --> 00:57:04,210
and return to
the World of the Living.

869
00:57:04,721 --> 00:57:06,245
That is the Shinenju...

870
00:57:06,389 --> 00:57:08,084
In other words... you!

871
00:57:09,292 --> 00:57:12,819
However, the Blanks do not lose
their individuality right away.

872
00:57:13,496 --> 00:57:15,098
Even though the Blanks
are basically empty vessels,

873
00:57:15,098 --> 00:57:19,364
they still wander for a time,
searching for their memories.

874
00:57:25,975 --> 00:57:27,772
This is where the problem begins.

875
00:57:28,644 --> 00:57:31,614
Placing the Shinenju at
the center of the Valley of Screams

876
00:57:31,614 --> 00:57:35,251
will activate the Blanks' natural desire
to seek their memories...

877
00:57:35,251 --> 00:57:38,121
and will drive them to
rush towards the Shinenju,

878
00:57:38,121 --> 00:57:40,589
causing the Valley of Screams
to contract.

879
00:57:41,357 --> 00:57:44,994
This force will be strong enough
to pull the World of the Living

880
00:57:44,994 --> 00:57:47,697
and Soul Society, which is separated
by the Dangai Precipice World,

881
00:57:47,697 --> 00:57:49,688
into a collision.

882
00:57:50,199 --> 00:57:51,188
What?!

883
00:57:52,034 --> 00:57:54,434
That's a disturbing thought...

884
00:57:55,471 --> 00:57:58,599
Furthermore, the contraction
has already begun.

885
00:57:58,908 --> 00:58:00,603
Never mind all the details.

886
00:58:00,910 --> 00:58:03,242
So what's going to happen?

887
00:58:03,880 --> 00:58:04,904
Who knows...?

888
00:58:05,248 --> 00:58:08,317
But two worlds that must stay apart
are going to collide.

889
00:58:08,317 --> 00:58:10,376
One will be destroyed if we are lucky.

890
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:13,421
Perhaps, both worlds will be destroyed.

891
00:58:13,656 --> 00:58:16,386
How much time do we have?

892
00:58:16,859 --> 00:58:19,726
I don't have enough data,
so I can't say with certainty...

893
00:58:20,129 --> 00:58:22,495
But I'd guess... about one hour.

894
00:58:23,733 --> 00:58:26,668
I'll mobilize the Punishment Force and
enter the Valley of Screams immediately!

895
00:58:27,103 --> 00:58:28,365
It's useless.

896
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:30,973
There is no Senkaimon that connects

897
00:58:30,973 --> 00:58:33,342
the Soul Society to
the Valley of Screams,

898
00:58:33,342 --> 00:58:35,867
therefore we have no way to enter.

899
00:58:36,546 --> 00:58:38,741
Any effort will be for naught.

900
00:58:40,416 --> 00:58:44,352
The situation is critical!
Prepare the Kido Cannon!

901
00:58:44,854 --> 00:58:49,917
We must destroy the Valley of Screams
and the entire dimension connected to it.

902
00:58:50,059 --> 00:58:54,428
But if we do that, it will cause
massive damage to the both worlds!

903
00:58:55,431 --> 00:58:57,592
There is no other choice.

904
00:59:00,736 --> 00:59:02,397
No! Please stand back!

905
00:59:08,110 --> 00:59:11,079
What is the meaning of this?!
This is a captains' meeting!

906
00:59:11,514 --> 00:59:12,276
Be gone!

907
00:59:14,050 --> 00:59:15,449
My deepest apologies, sir!

908
00:59:15,818 --> 00:59:18,218
I will gladly accept any punishment later.

909
00:59:18,788 --> 00:59:22,087
However, I have crucial information
to report!

910
00:59:22,892 --> 00:59:24,994
The Substitute Soul Reaper,
lchigo Kurosaki, has discovered

911
00:59:24,994 --> 00:59:28,064
an entryway to the Valley of Screams
through the World of the Living...

912
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:31,500
and has gone there in order to rescue
Senna the Shinenju!

913
00:59:32,902 --> 00:59:33,766
I beseech you...

914
00:59:34,437 --> 00:59:37,031
Please send reinforcements
to assist lchigo Kurosaki!

915
00:59:38,207 --> 00:59:40,368
Well... but...

916
00:59:42,411 --> 00:59:44,845
I cannot allow that.

917
00:59:44,947 --> 00:59:46,175
Why is that?

918
00:59:46,849 --> 00:59:50,580
Mind you, I am not taking
the Substitute Soul Reaper's skills lightly...

919
00:59:50,786 --> 00:59:53,222
However, we have only one hour,

920
00:59:53,222 --> 00:59:57,059
and there is no guarantee that
we could enter the Valley of Screams,

921
00:59:57,059 --> 00:59:59,395
defeat the enemy and rescue
the Shinenju in that time

922
00:59:59,395 --> 01:00:02,057
even with the full force of
the Thirteen Court Guard Squads.

923
01:00:03,132 --> 01:00:04,690
Do not think poorly of me.

924
01:00:05,501 --> 01:00:06,991
This meeting is now over.

925
01:00:07,503 --> 01:00:09,972
All Squads will begin
emergency procedures.

926
01:00:09,972 --> 01:00:11,906
Prepare the Kido Cannon!

927
01:00:50,112 --> 01:00:53,138
- I'm...
- I'm... going, too!

928
01:00:53,783 --> 01:00:56,377
I'm not about to let him
take all the glory.

929
01:01:19,375 --> 01:01:23,106
Lord Ganryu, the Blanks have
latched onto the Shinenju.

930
01:01:24,080 --> 01:01:24,910
Yes.

931
01:01:32,922 --> 01:01:34,355
Humph! A small fry, I see...

932
01:01:37,259 --> 01:01:38,658
Senna!

933
01:01:39,929 --> 01:01:41,123
I'm coming!

934
01:01:54,243 --> 01:01:56,211
Have you returned for
another beating?

935
01:01:56,612 --> 01:01:57,943
Give Senna back!

936
01:02:04,653 --> 01:02:08,817
Just when we were trying
to awaken her as Shinenju...

937
01:02:09,058 --> 01:02:10,359
Because of you,

938
01:02:10,359 --> 01:02:14,090
she will now suffer pain and
fear as a human being.

939
01:02:16,932 --> 01:02:17,830
Ichigo...

940
01:02:19,402 --> 01:02:20,334
What?!

941
01:02:21,070 --> 01:02:23,038
No...no!

942
01:02:23,172 --> 01:02:24,264
Senna!

943
01:02:28,244 --> 01:02:29,905
Nooo!

944
01:02:30,546 --> 01:02:31,774
You bastards--!

945
01:02:32,048 --> 01:02:33,310
Get outta my way!

946
01:02:51,867 --> 01:02:55,530
Maybe we should all go after Kurosaki.

947
01:02:55,938 --> 01:02:57,235
You better not.

948
01:02:57,706 --> 01:03:01,005
The Valley of Screams is
somewhat similar to the Soul Society...

949
01:03:01,177 --> 01:03:04,010
It's a spiritual world
where humans cannot go.

950
01:03:07,283 --> 01:03:08,375
Hmm?

951
01:03:11,253 --> 01:03:12,242
Kuchiki?

952
01:03:13,022 --> 01:03:14,319
Abarai!

953
01:03:15,324 --> 01:03:16,313
How was it?

954
01:03:17,560 --> 01:03:18,618
No good.

955
01:03:18,828 --> 01:03:21,464
Soul Society intends to
use the Kido Cannon

956
01:03:21,464 --> 01:03:24,024
to destroy
the entire Valley of Screams.

957
01:03:24,166 --> 01:03:26,396
If they do that,
what'll happen to Kurosaki...?!

958
01:03:28,337 --> 01:03:30,237
I won't let that happen.

959
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:35,106
Before they fire the Kido Cannon,
we'll go and finish the job.

960
01:03:35,811 --> 01:03:36,778
But...

961
01:03:37,446 --> 01:03:40,176
Don't worry. We'll figure something out.

962
01:03:40,316 --> 01:03:42,614
You wouldn't stand a chance
going in by yourselves.

963
01:03:44,386 --> 01:03:45,148
Oh!

964
01:03:45,554 --> 01:03:47,488
We've already put the team together.

965
01:03:48,023 --> 01:03:49,854
We'll settle this ourselves!

966
01:03:50,493 --> 01:03:51,926
I'm coming, too!

967
01:03:53,262 --> 01:03:55,355
There's no time. Let's go!

968
01:03:57,133 --> 01:03:58,100
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

969
01:03:58,801 --> 01:04:01,793
Kuchiki... Please take care of Kurosaki.

970
01:04:02,872 --> 01:04:03,896
I know.

971
01:04:31,700 --> 01:04:32,428
Let go!

972
01:04:40,242 --> 01:04:41,106
Dammit!

973
01:04:51,587 --> 01:04:52,451
Kenpachi!

974
01:04:52,888 --> 01:04:54,685
It's dangerous, over there.

975
01:05:01,297 --> 01:05:02,423
You too...!

976
01:05:03,766 --> 01:05:04,391
Huh?

977
01:05:06,735 --> 01:05:07,929
What was that?

978
01:05:18,147 --> 01:05:20,012
What's taking you so long?!

979
01:05:20,883 --> 01:05:21,815
You guys!

980
01:05:22,751 --> 01:05:25,345
You're not getting away with this...
coming all by yourself!

981
01:05:25,387 --> 01:05:29,187
Thought we'd join in for some fun.

982
01:05:30,292 --> 01:05:33,229
Look how many people
volunteered to the call.

983
01:05:33,229 --> 01:05:35,459
Leave this side to us!

984
01:05:35,998 --> 01:05:37,659
Now go, Kurosaki!

985
01:05:39,902 --> 01:05:40,926
I'm counting on you guys!

986
01:05:43,606 --> 01:05:44,800
- Let's do it!
- Right!

987
01:05:47,076 --> 01:05:50,170
Extend! Hozukimaru!

988
01:05:58,687 --> 01:06:00,154
Roar! Haineko!

989
01:06:10,799 --> 01:06:12,232
Raise your head!

990
01:06:12,468 --> 01:06:13,594
Wabisuke!

991
01:06:22,945 --> 01:06:24,708
Take that! You pesky brat!

992
01:06:35,658 --> 01:06:36,716
What's going on?!

993
01:06:37,226 --> 01:06:37,988
Hey!

994
01:06:41,063 --> 01:06:42,826
Is this what you're looking for?

995
01:06:44,700 --> 01:06:45,758
Why you--!

996
01:07:04,253 --> 01:07:05,652
You little--!

997
01:07:18,367 --> 01:07:20,665
It's too late! There!

998
01:07:44,326 --> 01:07:45,418
Ridiculous...

999
01:07:48,430 --> 01:07:49,260
What?!

1000
01:07:51,533 --> 01:07:54,593
I don't like playing tag,
but I'm not bad at it!

1001
01:07:59,241 --> 01:08:00,936
Go, Kenny!

1002
01:08:02,611 --> 01:08:04,203
Can I cut you already?

1003
01:08:04,646 --> 01:08:05,613
Dammit!

1004
01:08:09,752 --> 01:08:10,776
What do you know?

1005
01:08:11,320 --> 01:08:13,447
You might just turn out to
be some fun, after all.

1006
01:08:36,044 --> 01:08:39,844
Reign over the frosted heavens!
Hyorinmaru!

1007
01:08:50,659 --> 01:08:52,490
Hanging in there, huh, kid?

1008
01:08:52,761 --> 01:08:56,754
Let's see who'll last longer, shall we?

1009
01:08:56,932 --> 01:09:00,060
Well, I don't mind if this
keeps up forever.

1010
01:09:00,803 --> 01:09:01,667
Take this!

1011
01:09:33,469 --> 01:09:35,437
Humph... Looks like it's over--

1012
01:09:44,713 --> 01:09:45,771
Bankai!

1013
01:09:46,582 --> 01:09:48,914
Daigurenhyorinmaru!

1014
01:09:49,718 --> 01:09:53,176
Dammit! I can't believe
he still has that kind of power left!

1015
01:09:54,690 --> 01:09:55,748
What's going on?!

1016
01:09:56,291 --> 01:09:57,019
What?!

1017
01:10:14,776 --> 01:10:16,300
Third chant complete.

1018
01:10:16,578 --> 01:10:18,307
We are ready to fire.

1019
01:10:20,516 --> 01:10:22,017
Research Technology
CommCenter reports

1020
01:10:22,017 --> 01:10:24,952
the target will pass out of
critical range in five minutes.

1021
01:10:28,924 --> 01:10:29,856
Head Captain!

1022
01:10:30,192 --> 01:10:31,625
I understand.

1023
01:10:31,927 --> 01:10:35,624
I will wait until the very last second.
However...

1024
01:10:45,340 --> 01:10:47,831
I said I won't let you get
to the Shinenju!

1025
01:10:52,180 --> 01:10:53,374
Ichigo, grab on!

1026
01:11:04,993 --> 01:11:05,789
What?!

1027
01:11:06,194 --> 01:11:06,990
Renji!

1028
01:11:07,162 --> 01:11:08,959
Go! Ichigo!

1029
01:11:11,967 --> 01:11:12,934
What?!

1030
01:11:14,970 --> 01:11:16,369
You're not going anywhere!

1031
01:11:20,576 --> 01:11:23,067
Then we'll finish you two first!

1032
01:11:34,222 --> 01:11:35,120
What?!

1033
01:11:49,104 --> 01:11:51,800
Senna!

1034
01:11:52,507 --> 01:11:55,999
You still believe you can
save the Shinenju?

1035
01:11:56,712 --> 01:11:59,875
Damn right!
I'm gonna save Senna!

1036
01:12:06,455 --> 01:12:07,683
It's too late!

1037
01:12:08,323 --> 01:12:12,316
The Shinenju has already begun
to merge with the Valley of Screams.

1038
01:12:12,728 --> 01:12:15,424
No one can stop it now.

1039
01:12:15,931 --> 01:12:18,491
Shaddup! You just wait, Senna!

1040
01:12:18,700 --> 01:12:20,634
I'll get you outta here real soon!

1041
01:12:21,336 --> 01:12:23,702
You still don't seem to understand.

1042
01:12:24,106 --> 01:12:26,006
How useless it is.

1043
01:12:26,308 --> 01:12:28,469
Getsugatensho!

1044
01:12:33,749 --> 01:12:35,046
Why you--!

1045
01:12:36,351 --> 01:12:38,114
So you finally showed yourself!

1046
01:12:39,154 --> 01:12:42,248
I'll beat you and save Senna!

1047
01:12:43,158 --> 01:12:44,625
Go ahead, bring it on!

1048
01:12:45,360 --> 01:12:46,224
Let's go!

1049
01:12:46,528 --> 01:12:48,553
Ban...kai!

1050
01:12:57,339 --> 01:12:58,704
Tensazangetsu!

1051
01:13:46,288 --> 01:13:48,990
For a millennium,
our clan was forced

1052
01:13:48,990 --> 01:13:53,689
to nest in the crevices of
the Dangai Precipice World in disgrace.

1053
01:13:54,563 --> 01:13:59,193
We were able to endure
that suffering until this day...

1054
01:13:59,634 --> 01:14:04,765
because of our hatred...
our desire to destroy Soul Society!

1055
01:14:05,140 --> 01:14:08,871
And that moment is about to happen!

1056
01:14:09,511 --> 01:14:11,570
I will not let you interfere!

1057
01:14:21,757 --> 01:14:24,225
Why are you so determined?

1058
01:14:24,593 --> 01:14:27,796
The Shinenju is just
a collective of memories.

1059
01:14:27,796 --> 01:14:30,492
A mere remains of what
used to be alive.

1060
01:14:32,167 --> 01:14:33,634
That's not true!

1061
01:14:34,369 --> 01:14:35,301
Senna is...

1062
01:14:35,837 --> 01:14:38,499
Senna is here and she's alive!

1063
01:14:44,546 --> 01:14:47,913
She was confused and afraid,
looking for help...

1064
01:14:48,917 --> 01:14:51,010
I'm going to protect her...

1065
01:14:52,788 --> 01:14:56,155
I swore it on my soul!

1066
01:15:16,745 --> 01:15:17,905
I get it now...

1067
01:15:18,747 --> 01:15:22,342
All of you are just...

1068
01:15:22,784 --> 01:15:24,877
Ichigo!

1069
01:15:35,197 --> 01:15:37,290
We pass out of critical range
in two minutes!

1070
01:15:37,666 --> 01:15:40,100
No word yet?
What are they doing?!

1071
01:15:42,103 --> 01:15:44,765
I can wait no longer!

1072
01:15:45,540 --> 01:15:46,529
Sensei!

1073
01:15:49,177 --> 01:15:51,737
Fire the Kido Cannon!

1074
01:16:19,274 --> 01:16:20,036
Captain!

1075
01:16:20,342 --> 01:16:23,368
The cannon's been fired!
The entire dimension will collapse!

1076
01:16:30,986 --> 01:16:31,884
What?!

1077
01:16:36,558 --> 01:16:38,890
My zanpaku-to is pretty tough.

1078
01:16:39,427 --> 01:16:42,794
That kind of attack
won't change a thing!

1079
01:16:54,442 --> 01:16:55,966
You're not getting away!

1080
01:16:56,711 --> 01:16:58,076
There's no need to run away!

1081
01:16:58,546 --> 01:16:59,342
You impudent--!

1082
01:17:00,115 --> 01:17:03,050
Dance! Sodenoshirayuki!

1083
01:17:05,453 --> 01:17:06,681
It's useless!

1084
01:17:07,589 --> 01:17:08,851
Somenomai.

1085
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:11,918
Tsukishiro!

1086
01:17:36,685 --> 01:17:37,583
What?!

1087
01:17:38,386 --> 01:17:40,616
Like I said, it's useless!

1088
01:17:40,789 --> 01:17:41,448
Take this!

1089
01:17:49,230 --> 01:17:50,197
Brother!

1090
01:17:53,501 --> 01:17:55,036
Be honored...

1091
01:17:55,036 --> 01:17:57,971
that you will perish by my Bankai.

1092
01:17:58,740 --> 01:18:01,504
Scatter! Senbonzakurakageyoshi.

1093
01:18:08,750 --> 01:18:09,614
Brother!

1094
01:18:10,485 --> 01:18:11,315
Let's go.

1095
01:18:16,257 --> 01:18:17,224
Senna!

1096
01:18:42,083 --> 01:18:43,050
Here I come!

1097
01:18:45,053 --> 01:18:46,020
Come on!

1098
01:19:22,991 --> 01:19:25,050
Hey, you're awfully quiet.

1099
01:19:25,860 --> 01:19:27,589
What's the matter,
cat got your tongue?

1100
01:19:34,235 --> 01:19:35,566
Shut up.

1101
01:19:45,080 --> 01:19:46,308
They're coming back.

1102
01:20:13,842 --> 01:20:15,673
They've successfully retrieved
the Shinenju!

1103
01:20:15,777 --> 01:20:17,711
The Valley of Screams
is disintegrating!

1104
01:20:46,741 --> 01:20:47,571
Welcome home!

1105
01:20:48,143 --> 01:20:49,167
Sis!

1106
01:20:50,445 --> 01:20:52,072
Kurosaki, you did it!

1107
01:20:53,481 --> 01:20:56,006
Well done. You did it!

1108
01:20:56,084 --> 01:20:56,846
Quite impressive.

1109
01:20:57,485 --> 01:20:59,419
I'm so glad everyone is all right.

1110
01:21:00,488 --> 01:21:02,820
Thanks! Rukia! Renji!

1111
01:21:03,324 --> 01:21:05,884
Stupid! We didn't do it for you.

1112
01:21:06,861 --> 01:21:09,762
I must admit,
not bad for the freeloader.

1113
01:21:09,898 --> 01:21:10,887
What?!

1114
01:21:10,965 --> 01:21:12,557
You can stay and eat.

1115
01:21:13,268 --> 01:21:15,634
Senna! I forgot, your ribbon...

1116
01:21:18,806 --> 01:21:19,704
Ichigo...

1117
01:21:28,483 --> 01:21:31,611
What is it?
Why won't the alarm stop?

1118
01:21:34,222 --> 01:21:35,290
It's no good!

1119
01:21:35,290 --> 01:21:37,815
The dimension passed beyond
the critical zone!

1120
01:21:37,992 --> 01:21:39,494
Gravity was created and is pulling

1121
01:21:39,494 --> 01:21:42,088
the World of the Living and the Soul Society
together on a collision course!

1122
01:21:42,564 --> 01:21:43,588
At this rate...!

1123
01:21:48,570 --> 01:21:49,764
What's going on?!

1124
01:21:50,638 --> 01:21:51,832
It's not stopping?!

1125
01:21:52,941 --> 01:21:54,465
Then what'll happen?

1126
01:21:55,109 --> 01:21:56,474
This is not good.

1127
01:21:57,946 --> 01:21:58,878
Wait!

1128
01:22:03,952 --> 01:22:04,941
Why?!

1129
01:22:09,924 --> 01:22:11,084
This is bad.

1130
01:22:11,326 --> 01:22:13,692
Dammit! Is it too late?

1131
01:22:32,580 --> 01:22:35,014
Ichigo... I'm scared.

1132
01:22:36,251 --> 01:22:37,081
Senna?

1133
01:22:37,952 --> 01:22:40,182
But... But...

1134
01:22:41,990 --> 01:22:43,116
I won't let it happen.

1135
01:22:43,491 --> 01:22:45,322
Not when it's such a wonderful world.

1136
01:22:46,594 --> 01:22:49,859
Not when...
so many people live in it.

1137
01:22:51,032 --> 01:22:52,056
Not when...

1138
01:22:54,435 --> 01:22:57,063
You live here, lchigo...!

1139
01:23:01,709 --> 01:23:02,733
It's okay.

1140
01:23:03,311 --> 01:23:05,905
The Blanks are still near me.

1141
01:23:06,848 --> 01:23:09,578
If I release their energy all at once,

1142
01:23:10,184 --> 01:23:13,210
the two worlds can probably
be returned to normal.

1143
01:23:14,656 --> 01:23:15,520
Senna?!

1144
01:23:17,925 --> 01:23:21,656
If there's no world, you'll be gone, too...

1145
01:23:24,899 --> 01:23:26,696
I don't want that.

1146
01:23:31,539 --> 01:23:33,473
Stop! You still have...

1147
01:23:34,676 --> 01:23:38,339
I don't want you to die instead of me!

1148
01:23:42,083 --> 01:23:43,015
Senna...

1149
01:23:43,685 --> 01:23:45,243
Senna!

1150
01:23:52,527 --> 01:23:54,829
Countless explosions in
the Dangai Precipice World

1151
01:23:54,829 --> 01:23:56,064
have been confirmed!

1152
01:23:56,064 --> 01:23:57,699
The Soul Society and
the World of the Living

1153
01:23:57,699 --> 01:23:59,724
are both moving
towards their respective stable positions.

1154
01:24:00,902 --> 01:24:03,166
The collision has been averted!

1155
01:24:05,540 --> 01:24:08,441
Ichigo, I have a favor to ask.

1156
01:24:47,382 --> 01:24:50,715
I want you to check...
my family grave...

1157
01:24:52,453 --> 01:24:55,889
Remember yesterday,
I told you it was here?

1158
01:24:57,759 --> 01:25:01,559
I was alive once for sure...
and I lived in this town...

1159
01:25:02,630 --> 01:25:03,460
So...

1160
01:25:03,898 --> 01:25:04,523
Yeah.

1161
01:25:06,601 --> 01:25:10,867
I must've had a family.

1162
01:25:13,608 --> 01:25:15,576
I existed.

1163
01:25:17,111 --> 01:25:20,569
So there should be
a name on the grave...

1164
01:25:24,919 --> 01:25:25,886
Was it around here?

1165
01:25:27,255 --> 01:25:29,450
The fourth one from the end.

1166
01:25:36,197 --> 01:25:38,097
Is there... a name?

1167
01:25:39,667 --> 01:25:42,659
My vision is blurred...

1168
01:25:50,812 --> 01:25:51,801
Is it there?

1169
01:25:54,182 --> 01:25:56,275
Yeah, it's here.

1170
01:25:59,620 --> 01:26:01,315
You lived in this town.

1171
01:26:02,623 --> 01:26:04,147
You had a family, too.

1172
01:26:10,865 --> 01:26:11,991
I'm glad...

1173
01:26:21,843 --> 01:26:23,037
It feels so warm.

1174
01:26:25,379 --> 01:26:28,610
We'll... meet again, won't we?

1175
01:26:29,283 --> 01:26:32,377
What're you saying?
Of course...

1176
01:27:08,523 --> 01:27:11,583
The Blanks' energy will
soon be depleted...

1177
01:27:13,327 --> 01:27:16,163
And everything about Senna...

1178
01:27:16,163 --> 01:27:18,461
will fade from our memories.

1179
01:27:19,433 --> 01:27:23,529
Memories of those that never existed
can't possibly remain...

1180
01:27:29,710 --> 01:27:33,202
I know she'll be gone soon,
but right now...

1181
01:27:33,915 --> 01:27:35,473
I can still hear her voice.

1182
01:27:49,482 --> 01:27:52,719
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1183
01:27:52,719 --> 01:27:55,950
repeating and wandering through

1184
01:27:56,156 --> 01:28:00,560
The single answer I've found is

1185
01:28:00,560 --> 01:28:06,566
no matter how scared, or hurt I become,

1186
01:28:06,566 --> 01:28:10,502
I tell the person I love, "l love you"

1187
01:28:32,859 --> 01:28:39,332
I don't care whether you
"do love me, or do not love me"

1188
01:28:39,332 --> 01:28:44,504
In this world, there are way too many
things that cannot be changed,

1189
01:28:44,504 --> 01:28:46,539
no matter how hard you wish

1190
01:28:46,539 --> 01:28:50,210
And the fact that I love you

1191
01:28:50,210 --> 01:28:55,978
Is the truth that cannot
be changed by anyone

1192
01:28:59,019 --> 01:29:01,888
Crossing over a thousand nights,

1193
01:29:01,888 --> 01:29:08,919
I want to tell you,
I have to tell you

1194
01:29:09,029 --> 01:29:11,698
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1195
01:29:11,698 --> 01:29:15,135
repeating and wandering

1196
01:29:15,135 --> 01:29:19,606
The single answer I've found is

1197
01:29:19,606 --> 01:29:25,636
no matter how scared, or hurt I become,

1198
01:29:25,745 --> 01:29:29,738
I tell the person I love, "l love you"

1199
01:29:30,483 --> 01:29:36,156
It is scary to put feelings into words,

1200
01:29:36,156 --> 01:29:41,753
but I'll tell the person I love,
"l love you"

1201
01:29:52,472 --> 01:29:55,075
There is no way to express in words,

1202
01:29:55,075 --> 01:29:58,670
the joy of coming across each other
in this vast world

1203
01:29:58,778 --> 01:30:01,514
That is why we smile,

1204
01:30:01,514 --> 01:30:04,918
singing the passing colorful autumn
in sol-fa,

1205
01:30:04,918 --> 01:30:07,682
facing back against the winter,

1206
01:30:07,821 --> 01:30:10,957
waiting for the spring sunlight
through the trees,

1207
01:30:10,957 --> 01:30:15,291
in order to be reborn
So that we can protect someone

1208
01:30:15,528 --> 01:30:18,064
The path I came, and the path I go,

1209
01:30:18,064 --> 01:30:25,129
whenever I turn back
I had cowardly eyes

1210
01:30:25,305 --> 01:30:28,240
I want to face it,
but cannot be honest about it.

1211
01:30:28,274 --> 01:30:33,880
Repeating over the days of
not being able to love the person

1212
01:30:33,880 --> 01:30:40,053
But hating to be by myself,

1213
01:30:40,053 --> 01:30:46,049
I tried to love someone without getting hurt

1214
01:31:12,652 --> 01:31:15,188
Crossing over a thousand nights,

1215
01:31:15,188 --> 01:31:22,526
I shall go to you now,
there is something I must tell you.

1216
01:31:22,729 --> 01:31:25,432
I want to be loved, but don't try to love,

1217
01:31:25,432 --> 01:31:28,595
repeating and wandering

1218
01:31:28,768 --> 01:31:33,206
The single answer I've found is

1219
01:31:33,206 --> 01:31:39,212
no matter how scared,
or hurt I become,

1220
01:31:39,212 --> 01:31:43,615
I tell the person I love, "l love you"

1221
01:31:44,050 --> 01:31:49,989
Even if that feeling is denied,

1222
01:31:49,989 --> 01:31:57,418
telling the person I love...
is the most wonderful thing in this world.

1223
01:32:06,005 --> 01:32:07,495
Wow, what strong wind!

1224
01:32:23,756 --> 01:32:25,223
Oh shut up.

1225
01:32:25,258 --> 01:32:27,954
Who cares about that,
it's the same either way!

1226
01:32:28,461 --> 01:32:30,053
No, we'll get scolded!

1227
01:32:30,296 --> 01:32:32,093
Yeah yeah, I 'm out!

1228
01:32:32,599 --> 01:32:34,396
Hey wait!

